SIMIYU Region is planning to spend more than 6bn/- for the construction of dormitories to help female students from poor households attending secondary schools in the region. Speaking to residents of Maswa District in Simiyu Region at a public meeting held at Madeko ground recently, the Regional Commissioner, David Kafulila said that the construction of the dormitories will be implemented in the financial year 2022/2023. For his part, Headmaster of Nyalikungu Secondary School in the district Mr Giladius Michael Lwezaura said the girls have been facing myriads of challenges due to the lack of dormitories. In addition, Teacher Eliud Kabengo said that often when the students return home after classes, they have been subjected to domestic work, which deny them revision and study time. Citizens in the district have praised the government's plan to build dormitories for girls, saying the move will help the check the problem of teenage pregnancies.